WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.000
And so we've decided, like, these functions aren't really that great, so we've superseded

00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:07.000
them.

00:00:07.000 --> 00:00:13.120
So if you're not familiar with what that means, that means they are not going away, they're

00:00:13.120 --> 00:00:19.320
not deprecated, they're not on a path to being removed, but we don't recommend them anymore.

00:00:19.320 --> 00:00:23.440
So in some sense, these functions are like the safest functions to use because we're

00:00:23.440 --> 00:00:27.760
going to just put them away and we're never going to touch them.

00:00:27.760 --> 00:00:29.240
But we just don't recommend using them anymore.

